==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*līka-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[lik|līk]] (Dutch [[lijk]]), Old High German [[lih|līh]] (German [[Leiche]]), Old Norse [[lik|līk]] (Swedish [[lik]]), Gothic [[𐌻𐌴𐌹𐌺]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/li:ʧ/}}

===Noun===
{{Unicode|'''līċ'''}} ''n''
# ''(poetic)'' a (living) [[body]], especially the torso
# a dead body, a [[corpse]]

===Descendants===
* English [[lich]]

